pageTitle: Thanksgiving is peak day for cooking fires | PioneerNews.net
TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {29771=According to the National Fire Protection Association (NFPA), Thanksgiving is the leading day for home cooking fires. In 2010, cooking was involved in an estimated 156,400 home structure fires that were reported to U.S. fire departments. Those fires caused 420 deaths, 5,310 injuries and $993 million in direct property damage., 41200=Copyright © 2015}
